The paper discusses the use of genetic algorithms for optimization problems, which falls under the category of computational intelligence (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the adaptation of the algorithm to changing environments, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of information theory and minimum description length principle suggests a focus on machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The development of a special type of problem to test non-stationary optimization problems suggests a focus on experimental computer science (cs.DS). Finally, the discussion of algorithm design and optimization suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE).
